        <tr>
          <td style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.75;">
            <p style="margin: 0;">Dear President Trump,</p>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Thank <u>you</u>, for never backing down.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">You didn’t have to do this.</p>

            <p>You had everything. Peace. Comfort. Legacy.</p>

            <p>But you chose the fight. Not for yourself—for <strong>us</strong>.<br>
            <em><strong>For a country that was being sold off, torn apart, and forgotten.</strong></em></p>

            <p>You stood in the fire when everyone else ran. You took the smears, the sham indictments, the midnight raids. You never wavered.</p>

            <p><strong>And you did it for one reason:</strong><br>
            <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">To make America great again—not in slogan, but in spirit.</span></p>

            <p>So today, I don’t just say thank you.<br>
            I stand with you, ready to finish what we started.</p>

            <p>I believe in strong borders.<br>
            I believe in law and order.<br>
            I believe in energy independence, fair elections, and free speech.</p>

            <p>I believe <strong>you</strong> are the only one with the courage to lead this nation back from the brink.</p>

            <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold;">You fought for me.<br>
            Now I fight for you.</p>

            <p>Let’s take our country back.</p>

            <!-- SIGNATURE BLOCK -->
